      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;I'd like to see new and upgraded AAs for the warrior.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;1) A warrior should be able to at least hide in his surroundings.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Camouflage - 12aa - Passive - Years of training have taught you the ability to remain perfectly still, lower you breathing enough and blend into any surroundings well enough to remain undetectable to all roaming monsters.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;2) Often times or rather more often than not I am also the puller in the group. I'd like to see the warrior's run speed increased to at least 6 or 7 if not 8 like the Bards and monks which I can never find to pull for me.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Olympian Marathoner - 0/3 Levels - 5/7/9 aa - Passive - After years of travel across the planes of existence you have honed your skills at both speed and long distance running to match those of the best anywhere.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;3) If there is one thing that I am always short on it is endurance. Whether it be trying to solo and burning thru my discs as soon as they repop or in a group trying to keep agro off the zealous 20k critting wizard or in a raid with zerglings that can't follow simple instructions.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Endurance mitigation - 0/3 Levels - 5/7/9 - Passive - As mind and body become one you gain the ability, by sheer force of will, to lower the cost of endurance draining skills.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;4) We should be able to sell back previously spent AAs and reasign them to more important skills. There should be no cost involved in this. It would simply be a way to reassign &amp;quot;Wasted&amp;quot; AAs to &amp;quot;Needed&amp;quot; areas. Worse case scenario would be to make this an AA ability.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Alternate Ability Mastery - 12aa - Passive - Decades of experience have taught you the ability to clear your mind of old thoughts and focus on new tasks.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;</description>
