      <title>Re: DoDH AA's you'd like to see</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&amp;message.id=11287#M11287</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT face="Times New Roman" color=#808080 size=3&gt;[QUOTE}This AA's when activated creates a Knight very much like the Jesters. Instead of casting spells and telling lame jokes, the only thing the Maladroit Knight do is berate the Warrior. Constantly complaining about knights not having Defensive and goes on a campaign about have knights should have the ability to tank all bosses.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT face="Times New Roman" color=#ffffff size=3&gt;Finally an AA i can respect.&amp;nbsp; I am fearful that all the ideas given (good and bad) will be viewed by sony and taken into consideration.&amp;nbsp; They just prolly forget to give any kind of regen to keep the high costs up, making these skills/disc eye candy at best.&amp;nbsp; Mighty Strike is a perfect example,&amp;nbsp; Its just eye candy, with trivial dps improvments, which pretty much spells out your going to die, how well can you dps on your way out, and now with its second penalty of endurance, its not really useful in common situations, because cyclone blades and bazu below cost too much on or in a grind setting, so your limited to what you can use in disc type play.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;LoH aa..&amp;nbsp; Sir no disrespect, but plz log out and make a pally if you really want that, and Resolute Defiance is pretty much what your asking for now.&amp;nbsp; With the warriors curse of paying for using anything at all, your worse off for using it, then not.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Most of the things asked for are 1) should have been inherently given (better proc ratios), or 2) just more "extended improved stronger" versions of the stuff we have had since aa's were released.&amp;nbsp; How many aa's does a player want to dump in to a skill that is trival, and should have been good enough on the first set of aa's done.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Here are some&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;aa's I'd really like to see... &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;1) FD, hybrids want all our skills, lets start taking some of theirs.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;2) Snare, Rangers think they are good alt tanks (not), lets start snaring so we dont need them at all&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;3) Warrior Protection : Disc, or aa,&amp;nbsp; i dont care, just warrior only...&amp;nbsp; Is equal to Pally BBB group buff.&amp;nbsp; Duration equal to that of paly bbb, since people got in their head that having endurance ( MANA ) doesnt make them a caster.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;4) If you really want to over lay old aa's, do Finishing blow improvments, make it scale down from 68 to 50, instead of 55 being the cap, and yeah, supose you got to give rogs the same lvl adjustment, on assasinations&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;5)An aa called "press the attack" that actually interrupts the mobs casting, the current one is useless except for "real" trivial positioning, and heaven forbid the mob dont summon you past the center point.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;6)&amp;nbsp;Mounting Onslaught&amp;nbsp; (savage onslaught)&amp;nbsp; 100% each swing, each hit, each dps counted.&amp;nbsp; Something that actually works, for the endurance you waste.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;7) Carnage: combination of flurry and rampage. *Not /disc*, only aa&amp;nbsp; with a reasonable reuse time, not 48 hours 52 min, and 13 sec, like most of the really cool aa's&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;8) Potency Of the Shield&amp;nbsp; *note, i for one thing shields should only be done by a hybrid, warriors are axe swinging , blade slashing bad mofo's, not chicken shyt spell casters hiding behind caster protection type gear*&amp;nbsp; Anyways, IF you feel its a must for the war class.&amp;nbsp; Make this aa, "when equiping a shield, your primary proc rate is doubled, making your weapon proc twice as much as it normally does"&amp;nbsp; Least then it would be worth having one, although you lose a lot of your dps&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;9) War Paint : "Gleams your&amp;nbsp;Face with colors of war"&amp;nbsp;putting a WARRIOR ONLY proc booster. Should not be activated but more like the aa sturdiness or a very long duration.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;10) Sharpend Blades : increase to weap dps for a set amount of time, which is reasonable, and only if the endurance that we all know will get attached to it, isnt stupidly overtaxing&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;11) Collective barganing :&amp;nbsp; only the strong survive... aa that kills the weakest person in your group and heals you for twice of their hps.&amp;nbsp; Joking, but wouldnt that be funny to constanly kill the druids/rangers that are leeching exp night after night?&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;anyways, i am sure my aa ideas fall far short of some better thought out ones, but i would like to stop seeing aa's that just improve the same improved aa's used to improve aa's we got from the start, Or seeing stuff that is carbon copied and pasted from other classes.&amp;nbsp; Sure they want some of our trivial skills, but we are better than that and dont need their mana crap play.&amp;nbsp; Merlin never thought he was a warlord, and Aurthur never casted a spell, most ideology on mythic games/past/conceptions are based off such ideas.&amp;nbsp; If you want to play merlin... go lets hang out, if you want to play Aurthur, read aa # 11, :)&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
