    <item>
      <title>Re: DoDH AA's you'd like to see</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&amp;message.id=8643#M8643</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;I posted most of these on the General AA request thread on the Veterans Board, but here goes:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Channel Power: 2/4/8 Points&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Hotkey, 5/3/1 Minute&amp;nbsp;Refresh. Clicking it forces your next weapon swing to produce a proc (weapons with multiple procs will have the first proc go off). Gives Warriors the ability to introduce&amp;nbsp;some tactics with their weapons.&amp;nbsp;When soloing it gives you that needed Lifetap, when Raiding, it gives you a bit of snap aggro or the ability to interrupt a caster without being overwhelmingly powerful.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Intimidating Glare:&amp;nbsp;4 Points&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Hotkey, 10 minute refresh. Target runs in Fear for 30 seconds, scales up with level of the Warrior (at level 65, cannot Fear anything more than level 63, at 70, you can fear up to but not over level 68 mobs). Gives Warriors some Utility, while not infringing on Shadowknight and Necromancer core abilities. When soloing, it would be nice to have to give time to escape, when XPing, it can assist in survival with a bad pull, but the Refresh insures it isn't something that can be relied on for consistent use.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Dance of the Blade: 2/3/5 Points&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;2/5/10% of Crippling Blows land a Damage Over Time Component that deals 120/300/600 extra damage over&amp;nbsp;30&amp;nbsp;seconds (20 points, 50 points, and 100 points per 6 second tick). Does not stack, so Crippling Blows that land right after each other will overwrite the previous Damage over Time or it could get ridiculous with things like Mighty Strike (although maybe that's not such a bad thing). It's nothing in terms of overall DPS when you consider how few Crippling Blows a Warrior will actually land in a fight, but it does give solo warriors a bit more burst DPS and a little more flexibility to XP groups (I used to group with a Shaman and Cleric who kept me in a constant Berzerk state just for the Crippling Blows).&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Grudge: 1/2/3 Points&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;At each level of Grudge, you select from a list of NPC class types. All aggro effects are 125% effective against those class types. A quest will be available to allow you to reset your Grudges. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Bane: 3/4/5 Points&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Level 1 lets you select from a list of creatures. You do 1 Bane damage to those creature types. Level 2 lets you select from list again (you can pick up the same creature for 2 Bane damage or a different one for 1 Bane Damage). Level 3 provides the same opportunity a third time (Undead would specifically be excluded from this list, as that is the province of Clerics and Paladins. The creatures available on the list would generally be things like Gnolls, Goblins, Kobolds, nothing as general as 'Humanoid').&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Blind Fighting: 3 Points&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Passive AA, mitigates the effect of Blindness (instead of total darkness, light level is reduced but your screen doesn't go black)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Counting Coup:&amp;nbsp;3&amp;nbsp;Points&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Passive AA. Every humanoid killing blow (providing the mob gives experience)&amp;nbsp;provides you with a head of said humanoid (stackable) in your inventory. Turn in heads for tribute points.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Low Blow: 2 Points&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Hotkey AA, 1 min refresh, unresistable 0.0 stun to interrupt casting&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Zealotry: 6 points&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Hotkey AA,&amp;nbsp;variable effect and duration, 30 minute refresh. Depending on the God you worship, provides you with a different effect. Followers of Cazic Thule have a 1 minute Fear Aura, followers of Rodcet Nife would have an instant Complete Heal take effect, Agnostics would have a 1 minute 'zen' state where they achieve perfect form in&amp;nbsp;combat, with chances to Parry, Riposte and Strikethrough increased by a&amp;nbsp;certain percentage, and so on. Would actually give some meaning to Deity beyond cultural armor.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Hassan al-Nasir&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;House al-Nasir&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
